### Remaining Finding: `/research/[slug]` Still Missing `generateMetadata`

> [!WARNING]
> The case study pages **still do not export** a `generateMetadata` function. They inherit the global "PIS Labs | Applied AI Venture Studio" metadata from `layout.tsx`. This means:
> - Sharing `/research/credturn` on LinkedIn shows the **homepage title**, not "System Architecture: CredTurn."
> - Google indexes these pages with incorrect titles.
>
> **Required addition** to [research/[slug]/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/USER/Downloads/pis-labs/apps/web/src/app/research/%5Bslug%5D/page.tsx):
> ```typescript
> import type { Metadata } from 'next';
>
> export async function generateMetadata({ params }: { params: Promise<{ slug: string }> }): Promise<Metadata> {
>   const { slug } = await params;
>   const project = venturesData.find((v) => v.id === slug);
>   if (!project) return {};
>   return {
>     title: `${project.title} вЂ” Case Study | PIS Labs`,
>     description: project.description,
>     openGraph: {
>       title: `${project.title} вЂ” Applied AI Case Study`,
>       description: project.description,
>     },
>   };
> }
> ```

### Remaining Finding: Terms & Privacy Pages Missing Metadata

> [!NOTE]
> Both `/terms` and `/privacy` pages lack exported `metadata` objects. Browser tabs show "PIS Labs | Applied AI Venture Studio" instead of "Terms of Service | PIS Labs."
>
> **Fix:** Add a static `metadata` export to each page:
> ```typescript
> export const metadata: Metadata = {
>   title: 'Terms of Service | PIS Labs',
>   description: 'Terms of Service for PIS Labs, an Applied AI Venture Studio.',
> };
> ```

